{"id":14881182,"mediaExerciseId":"b1c43431-c6ff-4a29-aaef-6e8aaeee363c","exerciseName":"11","chapterName":"9","chapterTitle":"Net Present Value and Other Investment Criteria","groupId":612331,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":304,"solutions":[{"id":6063989,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"Capital budgeting is dependent mostly on the project's expected return. It's tough to get the exact outcomes because future cash flows are unpredictable.\n\nThe discount rate is used in several capital budgeting approaches Net present value, Internal rate of return, discounted payback time, the process of determining the ideal discount rate is difficult.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The payback period seems to be the most straightforward form of capital planning, this does not necessitate the calculation of future cash flows' present value, that is the amount of time the project will take to earn its costs.\n\nThe internal rate of return discounted payback period, and net present value is the most challenging capital budgeting methodologies, those approaches take into account the time worth of money, which can be tricky to compute.\n\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"a3dd84c4-3983-4bd7-baf6-e78bffc2ddfe","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":2}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corpo